      <h2>Decision Framework: Which Option for You?</h2>

      <h3>Step 1: Assess Utilization Needs</h3>

      <p><strong>Low Utilization (&lt;1,500 hours/year):</strong> Consider leasing (don't own underutilized asset)
      <br><strong>Moderate Utilization (1,500-2,000 hours/year):</strong> Either option (compare costs)
      <br><strong>High Utilization (2,000+ hours/year):</strong> Buying avoids excess lease charges</p>

      <h3>Step 2: Calculate Total Cost of Ownership</h3>

      <p><strong>Hire Purchase:</strong> (Monthly payment × term) + maintenance - resale value
      <br><strong>Lease:</strong> (Monthly rental × term) - deposit refund + excess usage charges</p>

